parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Headlight Dimmer Module (HDM) can cause the low beam headlights to fail, resulting in reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: The low beam headlights fail to operate
the low beam headlights dim or flicker
the high beam headlights work normally
other lights on the vehicle remain functional
and the failure may be intermittent.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical components to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: or malfunction; doors fail to lock or unlock; tire pressure monitoring system fails; ignition switch failure causes stalling or engine cut-off; blower motor failure; and other electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to stall or cut off, leading to accidents, injuries, or strandings.
symptoms: Engine stalls or cuts off while driving; ignition switch burns or fails; vehicle becomes stuck in gear; and difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights fail to illuminate; low beam headlights fail; high beam headlights function but low beam fails; and intermittent headlight failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Blower motor stops working; wires melt together on the resistor; and the entire plug melts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle are not adequately protected from the impact.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities to the occupants.
